  "articleSummary": "**Summary**  \nThe article is a hands‑on tutorial aimed at developers who need a quick, isolated database for local testing or legacy work. It explains how to spin up “throw‑away” containers (PostgreSQL, MySQL, etc.) with one‑line Docker commands, emphasizing the safety of sandboxed data and the convenience of avoiding cross‑contamination with production systems. While the guide is framed as a practical, step‑by‑step cheat sheet, it repeatedly warns that the examples are from 2015 and should not be used as production‑grade configurations; modern best practices (Compose files, pinned images, secrets, etc.) are mentioned as a contrast. The tone is instructional and slightly promotional, using the metaphor of “throw‑away” containers as disposable test labs for developers dealing with legacy code or security‑sensitive environments.",
